            <sentence>
                <offset>0</offset>
                <text>The patient presented at age 7 years for evaluation of short stature.</text>
                <annotation id="1">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0004322</infon>
                    <location length="13" offset="55"/>
                    <text>short stature</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>70</offset>
                <text>Review of her growth chart demonstrated prior stable linear growth below the 1.2nd percentile for age and sex (Figure 1).</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>192</offset>
                <text>She was born full term with a birth weight and length appropriate for gestational age.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>279</offset>
                <text>Examination revealed a stocky-appearing girl with a height of 117.5 cm (height SDS -2.5).</text>
                <annotation id="2">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="Comment">! Add term denied, https://github.com/obophenotype/human-phenotype-ontology/issues/10408</infon>
                    <location length="16" offset="23"/>
                    <text>stocky-appearing</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>369</offset>
                <text>Her arm span measured 118.4 cm, and arm span to height ratio was normal at 1.01.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>450</offset>
                <text>Her sitting height was 66 cm with a sitting to standing height ratio of 0.56.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>528</offset>
                <text>Her upper and lower segments were measured at 59.7 and 57.8 cm, respectively, giving her a normal upper to lower segment ratio of 1.03.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>664</offset>
                <text>Bilateral 5th finger brachydactyly clinodactyly, bilateral short broad thumbs and first toes, and mild mesomelia of the upper limbs were noted.</text>
